text: Corunna ( CORE-UN-NUH) is a city and county seat of Shiawassee County in the U.S. state of Michigan. The population was 3,046 at the 2020 census. The city is surrounded by Caledonia Charter Township and is slight east of the city of Owosso. ==References== Category:Cities in Michigan Category:County seats in Michigan
title: Corunna, Michigan
